Peru:
Fujimori has, once again, for medical checks into hospital
Former President Alberto Fujimori on Tuesday in a public hospital in order to investigate the muscle loss of his legs, informed his family doctor.
The 72-year-old Fujimori, who is serving 25 years in prison for breach of human rights during his government (1990-2000), has several diseases, including cancer of the tongue, which operates four times and is under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, a member of Congress, and his personal doctor, said the television that Fujimori investigated in Peruvian hospital Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas for three days, in order to determine the reason for his pain and muscle loss in the lower body.
Aguinaga commented that in his opinion, Fujimori could be pardoned for humanitarian reasons, yet he wished it not because it is innocent.
He was operated on four times of cancer of the tongue, and he has lost 18 kilos of weight and other diseases, such as a severe erosive Gastritis, a Zyste in neuronal kidney stones, high blood pressure and Durchblutungsprobleme in the legs, the doctor.
Fujimori is since September 2007 in the penitentiary Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the murder of 25 people by the Todesschwadron the Peruvian army during his government secretly was.
